node.text:
In almost every way measurable, millennials in the U.S. at 40 are doing worse financially than the generations that came before them.

Fewer millennials own homes than their parents did at their age. They have more debt — especially student debt. They simply aren’t as wealthy. 

Now, if predictions of a long, post-Covid economic boom are to be believed, this may be the last opportunity an entire generation has to build wealth before heading off into retirement.

node.title: Millennials Are Running Out of Time to Build Wealth to Retire

Taiwan is becoming a bigger issue between the world's two biggest superpowers. Taipei — a U.S. ally — and Beijing have avoided war for more than seven decades, but that balance is getting harder to maintain as China becomes more assertive in its desire for reunification.

Watch the full video at the link in bio to understand why analysts say Taiwan's status is "the most likely issue to draw China and the U.S. into a direct military conflict."

node.title: Why the Biggest U.S.-China Issue Is About Taiwan

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bloomberg Business on August 12, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'broke got fired and sued his firm for millions. Orso he thought. ICAP Bloomberg'.

node.text:
When Bruce Reid was fired from a job he says was paying him more than $2 million a year, he was eager to hit back with a wrongful termination claim. Years later though, the former ICAP swaps broker still hadn’t had his day in court.
 
At first his lawyer said a hearing in New York was moved because of a clash with a Jewish holiday. Then he blamed the lack of progress on a discovery dispute. Eventually he claimed he had begun settlement talks. 

None of it was true, including the existence of the suit itself. Tap the link in our bio for the full story.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bloomberg Business on August 12, 2021. May be an image of car and text that says 'Hackers return stolen stolenfundsfrom funds one of the biggest crypto heists ever Bloomberg'.

node.text:
On Tuesday, hackers stole about $610 million in what was likely one of the biggest decentralized finance thefts of all time. In an unusual twist, they’ve started giving it back.
 
About half of the amount has been returned, with the thieves pledging to hand back their entire haul from PolyNetwork — a DeFi protocol that lets users swap tokens across multiple blockchains.

The unidentified hackers also posted a Q&A online, saying they carried out the attack “for fun:)” and took the funds “to keep it safe” after discovering a bug in the code. Tap the link in our bio for more.

node.text:
Samsung unveiled its lineup for consumer gadgets coming in the second half of the year — including a flip phone it hopes will take the smartphone fight to Apple.

The 5G-capable Galaxy Z Flip 3 starts at $999, dramatically lowering the entry price for the foldable category.
 
Also coming before 2021 is out: The Galaxy Watch 4, and updated Galaxy earbuds. Tap the link in bio to take a look.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bloomberg Business on August 11, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'The manic Robinhood era is forcing quants obinhood to rethink popular trades ALL ÛALLS. ST. Bloomberg'.

node.text:
Between record dip-buying and the Robinhood roller coaster, the meme-stock army is running wild across Wall Street again.

Amateurs now command roughly one-fifth of U.S. equity volume, and some suspect the retail billions are undermining time-tested strategies like short selling and low-volatility investing.

The industry is in better shape compared to the dark days of the pandemic, and quant portfolios are more diversified than those run by human stock pickers. Yet there’s a palpable fear that the Reddit generation is getting powerful enough to disrupt the market patterns underpinning math-powered allocations. Find out more at the link in bio.

node.text:
JetBlue is making its first foray into transatlantic service, just nine days after the U.K. granted quarantine-free entry to vaccinated Americans.
 
The low-cost carrier is offering a one-way ticket from JFK to Heathrow from $202. A return trip on its business class service, Mint, starts at around $1,660.

The timing may seem strange, given that most Brits still aren't allowed to enter the U.S. But JetBlue isn't the only airline launching new services on the world’s most lucrative air route — and increased competition could mean better deals for passengers. Read in full at the link in bio.

node.text:
Audi's all-electric Skysphere concept vehicle has a notable feature: The driver can pick the length of its wheelbase.
 
In long mode you get a spacious, self-driving touring car. Push a button and it shrinks by 250mm (nearly 10 inches), reveals a steering wheel and pedals, and transforms into a sports car.
 
Inside, the cabin comes with a 1.4m (55-inch) dashboard for screening movies or hosting conference calls, and enough microfiber fabric and eucalyptus wood accents to make it feel like a private lounge. Tap the link in our bio to see more.

node.text:
The pass rate for the final level of the chartered financial analyst exam has plunged to a historic low after the pandemic played havoc with candidates’ preparations.

Only 42% of applicants passed Level III in May and June, the lowest ever for the test, which has been administered since 1963. It was the first time the final part of the exam was given using computers, and the success rate was down from 56% in December, when it was still administered on paper. The results are in line with pass rates for Level I and II, which also slid. Read more at the link in bio.

node.text:
Across the U.S., hospitals are running out of intensive-care beds.

Delta's march began in the U.S. in the Ozarks and South, in states and regions with low vaccination rates. But the surge has shown that even the best vaccinated areas still don’t have enough immunity against the highly transmissible variant.
 
It’s clear the pandemic isn’t done with America, particularly in places where residents have shunned shots or resisted the renewal of mask mandates and other public-health measures. In a few states, the unvaccinated are entering intensive care at rates matching the winter wave. Tap the link in our bio for state-by-state data.

node.text:
The majority of Morgan Stanley interns in Europe and the U.S. want to work flexibly when they enter the workforce full time, according to a survey.

There's one issue: their boss, CEO James Gorman, wants them back in the office. 

While Gorman said in July the bank "would be flexible where flexibility was called for," he has joined other Wall Street executives in making it clear that he expects his workforce to return — at least, largely — to the office, assuming it is safe to do so.
 
Someone’s going to wind up disappointed. More at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bloomberg Business on August 10, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'OFTHE THE STATE New York Governor Andrew Cuomo OF resigns after harrassment allegations PEO SਬOT Governor Andrew M. Cuomo Bloomberg'.

node.text:
New York Governor Andrew Cuomo announced his resignation on Tuesday, bowing to pressure to leave office or face impeachment.

The move marks a stunning fall for his decades-long political career. For months, Cuomo had dug in, refusing to leave office even after New York Attorney General Letitia James found that he had violated multiple federal and state harassment laws. County prosecutors are weighing criminal charges, while accusers are considering civil lawsuits.

He maintained that he didn’t harass anyone but was “thoughtless” in the way he spoke to and touched women on his staff. Read more at the link in bio.

node.text:
EXCLUSIVE: Apple’s next iPhone lineup will get at least three major new camera and video-recording features: a video version of Portrait mode, the ability to record in a higher-quality format, and a new filters-like system that improves the look and colors of photos. They’ll also include a faster A15 chip and screen technology that could enable a faster refresh rate for smoother scrolling.

The camera features are seen as some of the biggest selling points for the iPhone 12’s successor, which is expected to go on sale in the next several weeks. Find out more at the link in bio.

node.text:
Lionel Messi is traveling to France after agreeing to join Paris Saint-Germain, according to The Associated Press.

The 34-year-old Argentina star is set to agree a two-year deal worth about $41 million a year, a source says, after his contract with his career-long club Barcelona expired.

Funded for a decade by Qatari sovereign wealth, PSG is one of the few clubs in the world that could finance the signing of Messi. Tap the link in our bio for the latest.
